<%- include('../partials/header') %>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-3">
  <h4 class="m-0">Import Stock (CSV)</h4>
  <a href="/stock" class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary">← Back to Ready Stock</a>
</div>

<div class="card mb-3" style="max-width:760px">
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="text-muted mb-2">Upload a CSV to bulk-set product stock quantities. Rows are matched by <code>code</code>:</p>
    <ul class="text-muted small">
      <li><strong>Existing code</strong> → stock is set to the <em>absolute</em> value in the <code>quantity</code> column. Each change is logged as a stock-adjustment movement.</li>
      <li><strong>Same value</strong> as the current stock → row is skipped (no-op, no audit row).</li>
      <li><strong>Unknown / inactive code</strong> → row is reported as "not found" — no products are created.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-muted small mb-3">
      Tip: click <strong>Download current as CSV</strong> below, open in Excel, edit only the <code>quantity</code> column, save and re-upload.
    </p>
    <form method="post" action="/stock/import" enctype="multipart/form-data">
      <div class="mb-3">
        <label class="form-label">CSV file</label>
        <input type="file" name="file" accept=".csv,text/csv" required class="form-control">
      </div>
      <button class="btn btn-primary">Import</button>
      <a href="/stock/export.csv" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Download current as CSV</a>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card" style="max-width:760px">
  <div class="card-header">CSV columns</div>
  <div class="card-body small">
    <code>code, name, size, color, is_bundle, pieces_per_bundle, quantity, unit_label, reorder_level, notes</code>
    <ul class="mt-2 text-muted">
      <li><code>code</code> is required and must match an existing <em>active</em> product.</li>
      <li><code>quantity</code> is required — integer, the new on-hand total.</li>
      <li><strong><code>is_bundle</code> + <code>pieces_per_bundle</code> + <code>unit_label</code></strong> are
        <em>info-only</em> columns added to the export so you can tell at a glance
        whether the row's <code>quantity</code> means
        <strong>bundles</strong> or <strong>pieces</strong>.
        For a bundle SKU with <code>pieces_per_bundle = 5</code>,
        setting <code>quantity = 10</code> means
        <strong>10 bundles = 50 garments</strong> in real terms.
        These columns are <strong>ignored</strong> on import (they're just for your reference while editing).
      </li>
      <li><code>notes</code> is optional — appears in the stock-movement audit row. If left blank, the row gets an automatic "[CSV import] set X → Y" note.</li>
      <li><code>name</code>, <code>size</code>, <code>color</code>, <code>reorder_level</code> are also info-only — change them via <a href="/products/import">Products → Import</a> instead.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
